# Solidity Contract Guidelines

## Contract Architecture

This project follows the Tornado protocol architecture with the following key contracts:

- **Base Contract**: [Tornado.sol](mdc:contracts/Tornado.sol) - Abstract base contract with core functionality
- **ETH Implementation**: [ETHTornado.sol](mdc:contracts/ETHTornado.sol) - ETH-specific tornado mixer
- **ERC20 Implementation**: [ERC20Tornado.sol](mdc:contracts/ERC20Tornado.sol) - ERC20 token mixer
- **Merkle Tree**: [MerkleTreeWithHistory.sol](mdc:contracts/MerkleTreeWithHistory.sol) - On-chain merkle tree with history

## Key Patterns

- **Privacy First**: All contracts implement zero-knowledge proof verification
- **Merkle Tree Storage**: Uses incremental merkle trees for efficient proof verification
- **Commitment/Nullifier**: Uses commitment-nullifier scheme for privacy
- **Verifier Integration**: Integrates with [Verifier.sol](mdc:contracts/Verifier.sol) for zk-proof verification

## Security Considerations

- All deposits create commitments in the merkle tree
- Withdrawals require valid nullifier proofs
- Relayer support for anonymity
- Proper access controls and reentrancy protection

